content.description: Lower start to Trapeze Freak. Lose a star, add a grade. That's how it usually works right? Start in left hand jug slot and right hand 2 finger with pinchable opposing pocket. Move through some small holds and then into Trapeze Freak.
content.location: See Trapeze Freak

content.description: The name of this route is a guess.  It seems to be different in every guidebook I look at.  But I did not want to leave it out because, well, its there. Start just under the sloper on trapeze freak with a sharp two finger pocket in the roof for your right hand and a 3 finger sprag a the lip with your left.  Move straight up into sloper on Trapeze Freak then finish Trapeze Freak
content.location: Starts just right of Trapeze Freak

content.description: Awesome awesome awesome.  Start on obvious side pull and iron cross right to a sloper. Move through some crimps then dyno to the lip. BEST V8 IN THE PARK!
content.location: Starts just right on Double Clutchin

content.description: Don't know if this is a legit problem, but it actually feels like a better problem than Siege Tactics. Start on the jug (2nd move of Siege) and finish the same problem. Eliminates crux (V6 sit start)  and bumps it down a grade.
content.location: Siege Tactics (2nd move).

content.description: Start on Siege Tactics.  Move up to the left sloper and then left to a small crimp. Top out left on Queer Junkies.
content.location: Siege Tactics start.

content.description: Crux is definitely the first move.  Start low with left hand on an underclimb crimp/pinch and right hand on a greasy pocket.  Move up and right to a sloper. Then big move to another sloper. Finish straight up.  Definitely worth doing just so you can climb some of the few slopers in Austin.
content.location: Just to the right of Queer Junkies and to the left of Double Clutchin.

content.description: Start on sloping rails over the detached boulder. Climb small crimps to the top.
content.location: Over the detached boulder, left end.

content.description:
Start on Siege Tactics, traverse along horizontal break into Double clutchin and finish. fun pumpy problem.  

  can be done starting on either, feels the same difficulty either way to me
content.location: same start as siege tactics, bad pockets to the right of evil eye

content.description: Start on Evil Eyes and exit El Camino
content.location: Just to the right of the start for Left El Camino

content.description: Start on Queer Junkies and traverse right into Siege Tactics.  finish Seige Tactics.
content.location: See Queer Junkies

content.description: Starts low just right of Evil Eyes with right hand in a side pulling mono and left hand on a broken foot hold.  Move through cool crimps straight up to the top.
content.location: Just to the right of Evil Eyes and left of Seige Tactics

content.description: Start on Queer Junkies and traverse left into Evil Eyes.
content.location: Starts just right of Evil Eyes in a right hand side pulling mono and left hand on a broken foot hold.

content.description: Start on Queer Junkies and traverse right; finish on Double Clutchin.
content.location: Spacefarm. Queer Junkies start (sloper jug and mono).

content.description: Start standing on the little triangular boulder that faces the flake to the left of Local Plates, and jump from the boulder to the wall, over the trail, onto the jugs at the top of the flake. Don't miss
content.location: find the flake that's shaped like this < and the 4 ft tall boulder

content.description: Start on rail system.  Move straight up through sharp crimps.
content.location: Farthest left route on Spacefarm

content.description: Start on low slots with your feet behind a big broken off part of the wall. Move straight up to one of the tweakiest holds around.  Come into a good dish, establish, dyno to the slopey lip for a difficult top out (atypical for Mckinney)
content.location: Just to the right of Local Plates and left of Evil Eyes

content.description: Stand start on the 1st and 2nd pockets of Evil Eyes and dyno to the micro-crimp on the lip.
content.protection: Lots of pads and at least one spotter
content.location: On the 1st and 2nd pockets of Evil Eyes.

content.description: Start directly under the first pocket of Evil Eyes on the large pinch and crimp. Move into and finish Evil Eyes.
content.location: Start is to the right of Evil Eyes (low start) and to the left of Queer Junkies start.

content.description: Definitely one of the coolest lines at Mckinney.  Awesome features that will get your skin screaming! Start in a slot just right of Left El Camino and trend right through a crimp, good pockets, and then the Evil Eyes! Then hit the lip and the ride is over, so come back down and do it again.
content.location: Just right of Left El Camino.

content.description: Start Trapeze Freak Direct, traverse left on low pockets into Double Clutchin. Finish Double Clutchin.
content.location: Start Trapezius Freak

content.description: Start left hand in a good pocket and right hand in a good pocket that you kind of have to fold your fingers over to get into.  Big moves to good holds trending slightly right will lead you to the light!
content.location: Starts between Siege Tactics and Trapeze Freak.

content.description: Sit start on same good pockets as Double Clutchin' and move up and to jug. Continue moving up to another jug (slightly left) and topout.  **Beware of bad landing**
content.location: Same sit start as Double Clutchin'

content.description: Start Trapeze Freak, move up and left on small holds to the jug at the end of Double Clutchin. In keeping with the style of the FA, all future ascents must be done with a shoe on the right foot while left is barefoot. If you don't climb this with only one shoe, it's not a send.
content.location: right side of spacefarm

content.description: Sustained and pumpy
content.location: Start on obvious big flake for evil eyes direct , traverses right in the seam Finnish out  Double clutching

content.description: Probably the best wall at Mckinney
